parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and experience various electrical malfunctions, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
loses power
horn honks randomly
wipers malfunction
door locks unlock and lock randomly
dashboard lights flicker or go out
and various warning lights appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the battery and alternator can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and experience electrical malfunctions, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The battery drains quickly
the alternator fails to charge the battery
the vehicle stalls
and the electrical system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the convertible top can cause the top to get stuck in the up or down position, obstructing the rear view and making it difficult to operate the vehicle safely.
symptoms: The convertible top gets stuck in the up or down position
and the rear view is obstructed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag and TPMS systems can cause the airbag light to flash or remain illuminated, and the TPMS light to appear on the dashboard, which can be distracting and affect the safety of the vehicle.
symptoms: The airbag light flashes or remains illuminated
and the TPMS light appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission shift interlock can cause the vehicle to become stuck in park, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle won't shift out of park
the gearshift is stuck
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping or hesitation can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or slips when shifting gears
the vehicle loses power
the transmission makes a grinding or whining noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electronic throttle control issues can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or hesitates
the throttle body warning light comes on
the vehicle loses power
the engine RPMs surge or drop unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic throttle control can cause the vehicle to stall, hesitate, or accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The electronic throttle control warning light illuminates
the vehicle stalls or hesitates
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the accelerator pedal becomes stuck
the vehicle loses power
and the instrument panel lights may go out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to crash, resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the accelerator pedal becomes stuck
the vehicle loses control
and the brakes may not be effective in slowing the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
the engine light illuminates
the vehicle hesitates or loses power
and the instrument panel lights may go out.
